In [5]:
remove_index = False
for item in lines:
    if remove_index:
        id.append(item[0])
        country.append(item[1])
        description.append(item[2])
        designation.append(item[3])
        points.append(item[4])
        price.append(item[5])
        province.append(item[6])
        region_1.append(item[7])
        region_2.append(item[8])
        taster_name.append(item[9])
        taster_twitter_handle.append(item[10])
        title.append(item[11])
        variety.append(item[12])
        winery.append(item[13])
    else:
        remove_index = True
print("Initialize lists finished.")

COUNTRY¶
In [56]:
print("The second attribute: country")
print("This cloumn is nominal attribute.")
country_counter = Counter(country)
country_top5 = country_counter.most_common(5)
country_x = []
country_y = []
for i in range(5):
    country_x.append(country_top5[i][0])
    country_y.append(country_top5[i][1])
country_plt = plt.bar(country_x, country_y, color='lightblue', tick_label=country_x)
plt.xlabel("Country Name")
plt.ylabel("Count Number")
for a,b in zip(country_x, country_y):
    plt.text(a, b, b, ha='center', va='bottom')
plt.rcParams['savefig.dpi'] = 150
plt.rcParams['figure.dpi'] = 150
plt.rcParams['figure.figsize'] = (10.0, 4.0)
plt.title("Attribute country analysis")
plt.savefig("country_origin.png")
plt.show()
plt.clf()

The third attribute: description
This cloumn is nominal attribute.

Content of X axis:
1- This zesty red has pretty aromas that suggest small red berry, blue flower and a whiff of moist soil. The vibrant palate offers sour cherry, pomegranate and a hint of anise alongside zesty acidity and refined tannins.

2- Seductively tart in lemon pith, cranberry and pomegranate, this refreshing, light-bodied quaff is infinitely enjoyable, both on its own or at the table. It continues to expand on the palate into an increasing array of fresh flavors, finishing in cherry and orange.

3- Cigar box, café au lait, and dried tobacco aromas are followed by coffee and cherry flavors, with barrel spices lingering on the finish. The wood gets a bit out front but it still delivers enjoyment.

4- Stalky aromas suggest hay and green herbs, with raspberry in the backdrop. It's hot and short in terms of mouthfeel, with herbal flavors leading the way and berry fruit running behind. Dry red fruit and herbal notes dominate the finish.

5- Ripe plum, game, truffle, leather and menthol are some of the aromas you'll find on this earthy wine. The tightly wound palate offers dried black cherry, chopped sage, mint and roasted coffee bean alongside raspy tannins that leave a mouth-drying finish.

POINTS¶
In [12]:
print("The fifth attribute: points")
print("This cloumn is numeric attribute.")
points_missing = 0
points_remove_missing_list = points.copy()
points_remove_missing_list = [x for x in points_remove_missing_list if x!='']
points_missing = len(points) - len(points_remove_missing_list)
print("This attribute has {} missing value(s) with total items {}.".format(points_missing, len(points)))
points_remove_missing_list = np.array(points_remove_missing_list).astype(float).astype(int)
points_sorted = np.sort(points_remove_missing_list)
points_mean = np.mean(points_remove_missing_list)
points_median = np.median(points_remove_missing_list)
points_std = np.std(points_remove_missing_list)
print("[Attribute points] Mean: {:.4f}\t Median: {:.4f}\t Std: {:.4f}".format(points_mean, points_median, points_std))
points_cut_point = len(points_sorted)//4
print("[Attribute points five-number summary] Min: {}\t Q1: {}\t Q2: {}\t Q3: {}\t Max: {}".format(points_sorted[0], points_sorted[points_cut_point], points_sorted[2*points_cut_point], points_sorted[3*points_cut_point], points_sorted[len(points_sorted)-1]))
plt.boxplot(points_sorted, notch=False, vert=True)
plt.xticks([1], [''])
plt.xlabel('Points')
plt.title('Box plot')

In [22]:
print("Data value missing reason analysis:")
print("数据搜集的时候可能为网络问卷形式，部分属性的搜集可能为非必填项目，所以答题者没有填。")

Data value missing reason analysis:
数据搜集的时候可能为网络问卷形式，部分属性的搜集可能为非必填项目，所以答题者没有填。
In [23]:
print("According to the dataset, we hava 14 attributes.")
print("Remove the missing value is simple to act.")
print("These 14 attributes could have different relationship combinations.")
print("We calculate the correlation coefficient of each numeric match, then do the analysis work.")
print("Because of the randomness of dominal attributes, we do not use similarity between objects to fill in missing values of these attributes.")

According to the dataset, we hava 14 attributes.
Remove the missing value is simple to act.
These 14 attributes could have different relationship combinations.
We calculate the correlation coefficient of each numeric match, then do the analysis work.
Because of the randomness of dominal attributes, we do not use similarity between objects to fill in missing values of these attributes.

print("The coefficient matrix:")
print(coefficient_data.corr())

plt.bar(region_2_x, region_2_y, color='lightblue', tick_label=region_2_x)
plt.xlabel("Designation Name")
plt.ylabel("Count Number")
for a,b in zip(region_2_x, region_2_y):
    plt.text(a, b, b, ha='center', va='bottom')
plt.rcParams['savefig.dpi'] = 150
plt.rcParams['figure.dpi'] = 150
plt.rcParams['figure.figsize'] = (10.0, 4.0)
plt.title("Region_2 Remove Missing Value")
plt.show()
plt.clf()
